Suppose C ≠ C' in C_res(z) share Phi_w. Then at least one of the following holds:
  (i)   TIGHT: free-1 CS (w+1)-seam multi-mate (candidate top-seam / marked-incidence cell);
  (ii)  PARTIAL-PLANT: some c|n, c>=w+1, max_Q(C or C')>=1 (candidate planted/partial-factor cell; v8 witnesses live here);
  (iii) COSSET-FREE NON-TIGHT: neither core has a full c-fiber for any c>=w+1, and |C∩C'| < m−w−1 (remaining geometric wall; null/sparse high-prefix fibers on toys).
